Step 1: Draw a large rounded body shape near the bottom center of your paper.
Step 2: Add a big, rounded head at the top of the body, slightly tilted to one side.
Step 3: Draw two large floppy ears, one on each side of the head, starting from near the top of the head and extending outward.
Step 4: Add two big friendly eyes with small dots inside, positioned on the upper part of the head and between the ears.
Step 5: Draw a long, curved trunk extending downward from the center of the head, tapering to a rounded end.
Step 6: Add four sturdy legs extending down from the body, with the front legs slightly thicker and the back legs slightly shorter.
Step 7: Draw a small, curved tail at the back of the body, ending in a little tuft.
